Utilize a _class_ to colorize the word.

Here is _Wikipedia_ article on _SGR_ _control sequences_.\
_[Wikipedia &amp;ndash; SGR (Select Graphic Rendition) parameters](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ANSI_escape_code#SGR_(Select_Graphic_Rendition)_parameters)_

```java
class Word {
    String s;
    Set&lt;Character&gt; set = new LinkedHashSet&lt;&gt;();
    static String red = &quot;\033[31m&quot;, yellow = &quot;\033[33m&quot;, reset = &quot;\033[0m&quot;;

    Word(String s) {
        this.s = s;
    }

    void guess(char c) {
        set.add(c);
    }

    @Override
    public String toString() {
        StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();
        for (char c : s.toCharArray()) {
            sb.append(set.contains(c) ? yellow : red);
            sb.append(c).append(reset);
        }
        return sb.toString();
    }
}
```

And, here is an example usage.

```java
Word w = new Word(&quot;Brain&quot;);
System.out.println(w);
w.guess(&#39;i&#39;);
System.out.println(w);
```

